article.headline: Florida Atlantic 94, Savannah St. 68
article.story: BOCA RATON, Fla. (AP) -- Jeff Parmer and Paul Graham III had 18 points each to lead Florida Atlantic University over Savannah State 94-68 on Saturday. Florida Atlantic (9-14) got out to a fast start and seized an early 21-6 lead. FAU held the lead for most of the first half and led 46-36 at the half. Three other Florida Atlanic players scored in double figures. Carlos Monroe had 13, Sean Alarcon 12 and Xavier Perkins 11. Chris Linton led Savannah State (10-16) with 15 points.
